Strong mobilisation in Copenhagen and around the world for the climate
Tens of thousands of people demonstrated on Saturday to demand an ambitious and binding agreement on the fight against global warming, across the world and in Copenhagen, where police made several hundred arrests.
At least 30,000 people, according to the police, and 100,000 according to organizers, marched in the cold in the Danish capital, on the sidelines of the United Nations Climate Conference, which is due to reach an agreement by Friday that could come into force on January 1, 2013.
