Today we are taking to the streets to demand reparation for the ecological debt in favor of the South, explained Lidy Nacpil, a Filipino activist of the Jubilee South Coalition in Copenhagen.
We can't keep saying to ourselves: we have time, said the Beninese singer Angélique Kidjo.
There are rivers that are drying up in Africa, streams that you can walk on like you've never walked before.
