The turnout was 58% a few hours before the closing, according to officials of the Abkhaz Electoral Commission.
The first provisional results were to be announced in the night from Saturday to Sunday.
The five candidates in the race, including the incumbent president, Sergey Bagapch, categorically reject the idea of reunification with Georgia, which condemned the holding of the elections.
This election is a farce.
Georgian President Mikheil Saakashvili, for his part, "regrets that Abkhazia has fallen under the full occupation of Russia", his spokeswoman Manana Manjgaladze said.
Russia is the only country other than Nicaragua and Venezuela to recognize the independence of the territory of 216,000 inhabitants, while the rest of the world considers it part of Georgia illegally occupied by Russian troops.
After breaking away from Georgia in the 1992-1993 conflict, which left thousands dead, Abkhazia is seeking to show through this election that it is ready to join the international community.
