The Galeries Lafayette, which expect 200,000 customers every day, welcomed the fact that "the RATP is making efforts to serve the department stores".
The RER A runs west through the Paris agglomeration.
The RATP section runs from Saint-Germain-en-Laye and Nanterre to Boissy-Saint-Léger and Marne-La-Vallée.
On Friday, about one in two trains ran during peak hours, and almost no trains during off-peak hours, as expected.
As on Thursday, there was no commotion on the docks, as the French organized themselves.
In the early morning, the station of Saint-Germain-en-Laye (Yvelines) was much less frequented than usual, mainly because of the absence of students and high school students.
In Boissy-Saint-Léger (Val-de-Marne), Jack Nbakina, a 29-year-old engineer, said that he got up "a half hour earlier to make sure he got there on time".
The train station of Saint-Lazare was not saturated, according to the SNCF, which had planned a staffing of agents and law enforcement.
RER A operated by the SNCF from or to Cergy-Le-Haut arrived or departed from the Saint-Lazare station to join the metros.
