How much should you be paid based on your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can find out what salary they deserve based on their profile, thanks to a new application from Trovit, the search engine with the largest number of small ads for real estate, jobs and vehicles in Spain.
The tool  How much should you be paid?  calculates the salaries of users from the more than 140 000 job offers that Trovit has in Spain, from a form available on Facebook, where you have to register your profession, your years of experience, your age and the city where you want to work.
"We have been using the app for a week and the search engine has detected that, as a general rule, the Spanish worker feels that he is not well paid", said Albert Ribera, product manager at Trovit, in a statement.
According to data available to Trovità from its search engines in the UK and France, Spanish workers are the least paid.
A British computer programmer receives €45,226 in gross annual earnings and a French computer programmer €31,059, while a Spanish computer programmer receives €24,000.
Similarly, a driver in England receives a gross annual salary of €34,247, in France €25,751, and in Spain €16,420.
According to Trovit, the lowest-paid job in Spain is that of a waiter, with 11 592 euros net per year, followed by that of a salesman, with 14 725 euros, and that of a manual worker, with 15 667 euros.
The most popular jobs on the Internet over the past three months are driver, part-time and social worker.
